  "text": "There is a greater risk of nonunion and instability with conservative treatment. It has been demonstrated in some series that anterior odontoid screw or posterior cervical fixati- on achieved fusion in more than 80% of the cases [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . In another report, a fracture union rate of 100% was reported using posterior C1-C2 fusion [CITATION_3] .",
